name: #5 Palonopsia
description: Palonopsia (Greek: 'palin' >  'again' & 'opsia' > 'seeing') is the persistent recurrence of a visual image after the stimulus has been removed. The mountains are diverse and different every day, but they feel familiar. The music was inspired on the picture, composed while I was there. The visuals were inspired on the music, overdubbed on the picture. They are dynamic clojure(quil) patches, live coded in conjunction with live patched modular music.
